reg_info.full_title: O. Reg. 240/95: EXEMPTIONS FROM ACT - SIX NATIONS OF THE GRAND RIVER
reg_info.reg_name_text: EXEMPTIONS FROM ACT—SIX NATIONS   OF THE GRAND RIVER
reg_info.citation: O. Reg. 240/95: EXEMPTIONS FROM ACT - SIX NATIONS OF THE GRAND RIVER
reg_info.act_under: Child and Family Services Act   Loi sur les services à l’enfance et à la famille

content.content: 1. Despite subsection 3 (1) of the Act, a child and family service authority designated under subsection 211 (1) of the Act by the elected Council of Six Nations of the Grand River is exempt from the requirement that it be incorporated for the purposes of being approved and designated under clause 211 (2) (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 240/95, s. 1.
content.raw_html: 1. Despite subsection 3 (1) of the Act, a child and family service authority designated under subsection 211 (1) of the Act by the elected Council of Six Nations of the Grand River is exempt from the requirement that it be incorporated for the purposes of being approved and designated under clause 211 (2) (c) of the Act. O. Reg. 240/95, s. 1.

content.content: 2. A child and family service authority designated under subsection 211 (1) of the Act by the elected Council of Six Nations of the Grand River is exempt from subsection 46 (1) of the Act. O. Reg. 240/95, s. 2.
